Naimean_v3 Site Config / Codebase Overview
=========================================

Purpose
-------
Naimean_v3 is an interactive retro-themed website (naimean.com) built around a virtual "den" experience, with multiple room/pages and media-driven overlays.

Key Technologies
----------------
- Cloudflare Workers (server/runtime)
- Cloudflare Durable Objects (hotspot persistence)
- Static asset hosting from `public/`
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript frontend
- Node.js built-in test runner (`node --test`) via `npm test`
- Discord OAuth (session cookie auth)
- Optional Google Drive media integration for aquarium clips

Top-Level Structure
-------------------
- `src/worker.js`
  - Main Worker entrypoint.
  - Routes API endpoints and static asset requests.
  - Handles Discord auth routes, hotspots API, and aquarium media endpoints.

- `public/`
  - Main site pages and all static frontend assets.
  - Core pages include:
    - `index.html` (main den entrypoint)
    - `noahs-arcade.html`, `chapel.html`, `calendar.html`, `commodore.html`, etc.
  - Assets are organized under:
    - `public/assets/images`
    - `public/assets/video`
    - `public/assets/audio`
    - `public/assets/arcade`

- `test/worker.test.js`
  - Worker-focused tests executed by `npm test`.

- `functions/api/hotspots.js`
  - Legacy function location retained in repo.

- `wrangler.jsonc`
  - Cloudflare deployment configuration:
    - Worker main: `src/worker.js`
    - Assets directory: `public`
    - Durable Object binding: `HOTSPOT_STORE`

Routing + API Organization
--------------------------
- Worker-first routing is enabled for all paths.
- API routes are implemented in `src/worker.js`, including:
  - `/api/hotspots`
  - `/api/aquarium/shrimp-clips`
  - `/api/aquarium/shrimp-clip/:id`
  - Discord auth/session endpoints
- Static pages and media are served from `public/`.
- Aliases route den-related paths to the main den page.

How the App Is Organized Conceptually
-------------------------------------
- Frontend scene logic lives in HTML/JS files under `public/`.
- Backend control plane lives in `src/worker.js`.
- Persistent interactive state (hotspots) is stored through Durable Objects.
- Rich media (images/video/audio) drives the interactive experience.
